      • getContainersFromPreviousAttempts

        private java.util.List<org.apache.hadoop.yarn.api.records.Container> getContainersFromPreviousAttempts(org.apache.hadoop.yarn.api.protocolrecords.RegisterApplicationMasterResponse response)
        Checks if a YARN application still has registered containers. If the application master registered at the ResourceManager for the first time, this list will be empty. If the application master registered a repeated time (after a failure and recovery), this list will contain the containers that were previously allocated.
        参数:
        response - The response object from the registration at the ResourceManager.
        返回:
        A list with containers from previous application attempt.
